## Part 5: Usage Conditions (When to Use Each Font)

### Display Font (h1, hero text, large statements)

```typescript
// Use: Hero headlines, main titles, brand statements
export const displayUsage = {
  condition: "Very Large Text (>32px)",
  examples: [
    "Page Hero: 'Build faster with AI'",
    "Section Title: 'Why Choose Us'",
    "Call-to-Action: 'Get Started Today'"
  ],
  fontWeight: "600-700",
  letterSpacing: "-0.02em", // Tighten large text
  lineHeight: "1.2"
};
```

**CSS:**
```css
.hero-title {
  font-family: var(--font-display);
  font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  line-height: 1.2;
}
```

